The paper discusses the use of P2P overlays to provide a decentralized alternative to centralized social networks, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The focus on privacy and security through the use of a public key infrastructure (PKI) suggests a potential fit for the categories of security and privacy (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of overlays for friend discovery and bootstrap connections could also relate to the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
